# Braces on control flow

Always wrap the body of `if`, `else`, `else if`, `for`, `while`, and `do` in **curly braces**, even for a single statement.

Do **not** use one-line forms such as `if (cond) return x;`.

Oxlint enforces this with the `curly` rule (`["error", "all"]`) in `.oxlintrc.json`.

```typescript
// Avoid
if (!ready) return;
if (x) doThing();

// Prefer
if (!ready) {
  return;
}
if (x) {
  doThing();
}
```
